Given an integer n, return true if it is a power of four. Otherwise, return false.

An integer n is a power of four, if there exists an integer x such that n == 4x.

 

Example 1:

Input: n = 16
Output: true
Example 2:

Input: n = 5
Output: false
Example 3:

Input: n = 1
Output: true
 

Constraints:

-2^31 <= n <= 2^31 - 1
class Solution {
public:
    bool isPowerOfFour(int n) {
        if(n<=0)
            return false;
        if(n==1)
            return true;
        
        if((n&(n-1))==0 && n%3==1)
        return true;
        else
            return false;
    }
};
